ANTHRAX, BOVINE - KAZAKHSTAN: (TALDYQORGHAN)
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 30 Oct 2012
Source: OIE [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Diseaseinformation/Immsummary


Information received on 30 Oct 2012 from Dr Nurtazina Gulzhan, Deputy Chairman, Committee of Veterinary Control and Supervision, Ministry of Agriculture, Astana, Kazakhstan

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 15 Oct 2012
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 22 Oct 2012
Report date: 30 Oct 2012
Date submitted to OIE: 30 Oct 2012
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 14 Sep 2011
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Zhanalyk, Zhainak, Kerbulaksky, TALDY KURGAN
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Oct 2012
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 847 / 1 / - / 1 / -
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 847 / 1 / - / 1 / -
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate
Cattle / 0.12 percent

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection
* Swill feeding
* soil-borne infection
Epidemiological comments: By 29 Oct 2012, also vaccinated were: 4437 sheep/goats, 196 horses, 30 donkeys, and 100 swine.

Control measures:
Measures applied
* Quarantine
* Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
TALDY KURGAN / Cattle / 1172 / Done by 29 Oct 2012
* No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied
* Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Reference Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory) / Cattle / bacteriological examination / 22 Oct 2012 / Positive
National Reference Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 25 Oct 2012 / Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [Check OIE website; outbreak is in the southeast corner of Kazakhstan, north of Almaty and not far from the Kyrgyz and Chinese borders. - Mod.MHJ]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[This disease is a not uncommon occurrence in Eastern Kazakhstan, though overall, the annual incidence is decreasing.

Maps of Kazakhstan can be seen at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kazakhstan_pol01.jpg and http://healthmap.org/r/1hSb. - Mod.MHJ]
